quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  101,10,"And what do you know what that is?"
  101,11,"A Blazing Fire!{1}",footnotes:1:That is, it will not merely be a deep pit but will also be full of raging fire.
  102,7,"again, you shall most certainly end up seeing it with absolute certainty."
  102,8,"Then, on that Day, you will be called to account for all the bounties you enjoyed.{1}",footnotes:1:“Then” in this sentence does not mean that accountability will be held after the culprits have been cast into Hell
  104,1,"Woe to every fault-finding backbiter;{1}",footnotes:1:The words used in the original are humazat il-lumazah.
  104,2,"who amasses wealth and counts it over and again.{1}",footnotes:1:This second sentence after the first sentence by itself
  104,3,"He thinks that his wealth will immortalise him forever.{1}",footnotes:1:Another meaning also can be: He thinks that his wealth
